    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is this 2003 Porsche 911 (996) Carrera 4S, a wide-body icon featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six paired with a 6-speed G96 manual transaxle. Mechanically sound, this example has been updated with an LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a new rear main seal (RMS) to ensure long-term reliability. The naturally aspirated powerplant delivers 315 hp with a signature boxer howl, while the all-wheel-drive system provides exceptional mechanical grip through corners. The chassis remains taut, benefiting from the Turbo-derived suspension geometry and 'Big Red' four-piston monoblock calipers. Finished in Arctic Silver, the exterior shows minor road wear consistent with its mileage, while the interior leather retains its structural integrity with only light patina. This is a driver-focused machine with a sorted drivetrain ready for the open road.",
      "price": 34500.0,
